<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>NyayaAI Audit Report — {{ report.request.audit_id }}</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --saffron: #FF9933;
      --green: #138808;
      --navy: #000080;
      --ink: #1a1a1a;
      --muted: #666;
      --ok: #0a7b2e;
      --warn: #b45309;
      --fail: #b91c1c;
      --bg: #fafafa;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --border: #e5e5e5;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Noto Sans", sans-serif;
      color: var(--ink);
      background: var(--bg);
      margin: 0;
      padding: 40px;
      line-height: 1.55;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .report {
      max-width: 960px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: var(--card);
      padding: 48px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-top: 6px solid var(--navy);
    }
    header { border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 16px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .brand { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
    .brand .n { color: var(--saffron); }
    .brand .a { color: var(--green); }
    .subtitle { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 4px; }
    h1, h2, h3 { color: var(--navy); }
    h1 { font-size: 22px; margin: 32px 0 12px; }
    h2 { font-size: 17px; margin: 24px 0 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 4px; }
    h3 { font-size: 14px; margin: 16px 0 6px; }
    .kv { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr; gap: 6px 16px; font-size: 13px; }
    .kv dt { color: var(--muted); }
    .kv dd { margin: 0; }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 2px 10px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }
    .badge.pass { background: #dcfce7; color: var(--ok); }
    .badge.fail { background: #fee2e2; color: var(--fail); }
    .badge.warn { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--warn); }
    .badge.no-data { background: #f3f4f6; color: var(--muted); }
    .badge.none { background: #f3f4f6; color: var(--muted); }
    .badge.minor { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--warn); }
    .badge.major { background: #fee2e2; color: var(--fail); }
    .badge.info { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
    .badge.advisory { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--warn); }
    .badge.action_required { background: #fee2e2; color: var(--fail); }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 8px 0; font-size: 13px; }
    th, td { text-align: left; padding: 8px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    th { background: #f9fafb; font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.3px; color: var(--muted); }
    td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-family: "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; }
    .summary-card {
      background: #f0f9ff;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--navy);
      padding: 16px 20px;
      margin: 12px 0 20px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .slice-para { margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .slice-para .key { font-family: "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); }
    .reco { padding: 10px 14px; margin: 8px 0; border-left: 3px solid var(--muted); background: #fcfcfc; }
    .reco.action_required { border-color: var(--fail); }
    .reco.advisory { border-color: var(--warn); }
    .reco.info { border-color: #1e40af; }
    .reco .t { font-weight: 600; }
    .annex {
      margin-top: 32px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 16px 20px;
      background: #fafafa;
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .annex h2 { margin-top: 0; border: none; padding: 0; }
    .annex ul { padding-left: 20px; }
    .disclaimer { font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; margin-top: 16px; }
    footer {
      margin-top: 40px;
      padding-top: 16px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-family: "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace;
      word-break: break-all;
    }
    @media print {
      body { padding: 0; background: white; }
      .report { border: none; padding: 20px; max-width: none; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="report">
    <header>
      <div class="brand"><span class="n">Nyaya</span><span class="a">AI</span></div>
      <div class="subtitle">Algorithmic Fairness Audit — India-context bias report</div>
    </header>

    <h1>Audit {{ report.request.audit_id }}</h1>
    <dl class="kv">
      <dt>Model</dt><dd>{{ report.request.model.model_id }} ({{ report.request.model.task }})</dd>
      <dt>Dataset</dt><dd>{{ report.request.dataset.name }} — {{ report.request.dataset.row_count }} rows</dd>
      <dt>Regulatory regime</dt><dd><span class="badge info">{{ report.request.regime }}</span></dd>
      <dt>Requested attributes</dt><dd>
        {% for a in report.request.requested_attributes %}<span class="badge info">{{ a }}</span> {% endfor %}
      </dd>
      <dt>Goal</dt><dd>{{ report.request.goal }}</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>1. Executive summary</h2>
    <div class="summary-card">{{ report.narrative.summary }}</div>

    {% set di = report.result.overall_disparate_impact %}
    <dl class="kv">
      <dt>Overall disparate impact</dt>
      <dd>
        <strong>{{ di | fmt_ratio }}</strong>
        <span class="badge {{ di | ff_flag }}">
          {% if di is none %}no data
          {% elif di >= 0.8 %}passes 4/5ths rule
          {% else %}FAILS 4/5ths rule
          {% endif %}
        </span>
      </dd>
      <dt>Drift</dt>
      <dd><span class="badge {{ report.drift.level }}">{{ report.drift.level }}</span> — {{ report.drift.reason }}</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>2. Fairness metrics by slice</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Slice</th>
          <th>Metric</th>
          <th class="num">Value</th>
          <th class="num">n</th>
          <th>4/5ths</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for m in report.result.metrics %}
        <tr>
          <td><code>{{ m.slice_key }}</code></td>
          <td>{{ m.metric }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ m.value | fmt_ratio }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ m.sample_size }}</td>
          <td>
            {% if m.metric in ["demographic_parity_ratio", "disparate_impact"] %}
              <span class="badge {{ m.value | ff_flag }}">
                {% if m.value >= 0.8 %}pass{% else %}fail{% endif %}
              </span>
            {% else %}
              <span class="badge no-data">—</span>
            {% endif %}
          </td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>3. Per-slice interpretation</h2>
    {% for p in report.narrative.per_slice %}
    <div class="slice-para">
      <div class="key">{{ p.slice_key }}</div>
      <div>{{ p.paragraph }}</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}

    <h2>4. Recommendations</h2>
    {% for r in report.narrative.recommendations %}
    <div class="reco {{ r.severity }}">
      <div class="t">{{ r.title }} <span class="badge {{ r.severity }}">{{ r.severity }}</span></div>
      <div>{{ r.detail }}</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}

    <p class="disclaimer">{{ report.narrative.disclaimer }}</p>

    {% if report.counterfactual_narrative %}
    {% set cf = report.counterfactual_narrative %}
    {% set cfs = report.result.counterfactual %}
    <h2>5. Counterfactual fairness (individual-level)</h2>
    <div class="reco {{ cf.severity }}">
      <div class="t">{{ cf.headline }} <span class="badge {{ cf.severity }}">{{ cf.severity }}</span></div>
      <div style="margin-top: 6px;">{{ cf.interpretation }}</div>
    </div>
    {% if cfs %}
    <dl class="kv">
      <dt>Protected attribute</dt><dd>{{ cfs.protected_attribute }}</dd>
      <dt>Directional flip rate</dt><dd><strong>{{ "%.1f%%" | format(cfs.directional_flip_rate * 100) }}</strong> of {{ cfs.sample_size_used }} sampled rows</dd>
    </dl>
    {% if cfs.flip_rate_by_pair %}
    <h3>Flip rate by group pair</h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Pair (before → after)</th><th class="num">Flip rate</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for pair, rate in cfs.flip_rate_by_pair.items() %}
        <tr><td><code>{{ pair }}</code></td><td class="num">{{ "%.1f%%" | format(rate * 100) }}</td></tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}
    {% if cfs.examples %}
    <h3>Anonymised examples</h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Before</th><th>After</th><th class="num">P(before)</th><th class="num">P(after)</th><th>Decision</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for ex in cfs.examples %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ ex.row_index }}</td>
          <td><code>{{ ex.protected_value_before }}</code></td>
          <td><code>{{ ex.protected_value_after }}</code></td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.2f" | format(ex.probability_before) }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.2f" | format(ex.probability_after) }}</td>
          <td>{{ ex.decision_before }} → {{ ex.decision_after }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
    {% if cf.example_takeaways %}
    <ul>
      {% for t in cf.example_takeaways %}<li>{{ t }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
    <p class="disclaimer">{{ cf.disclaimer }}</p>
    {% endif %}

    {% if report.root_cause_narrative %}
    {% set rc = report.root_cause_narrative %}
    {% set rcs = report.result.root_cause %}
    <h2>6. Root-cause analysis (proxy features)</h2>
    <div class="summary-card">{{ rc.headline }}</div>
    {% if rc.top_drivers %}
    <h3>Top drivers</h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th class="num">Contribution to disparity</th><th>Why this matters in India</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for d in rc.top_drivers %}
        <tr>
          <td><code>{{ d.feature_name }}</code></td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%+.3f" | format(d.contribution_to_disparity) }}</td>
          <td>{{ d.plain_explanation }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}
    {% if rc.proxy_warnings %}
    <h3>Proxy-feature warnings</h3>
    <ul>
      {% for w in rc.proxy_warnings %}<li>{{ w }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
    {% if rc.suggested_actions %}
    <h3>Suggested actions</h3>
    <ul>
      {% for a in rc.suggested_actions %}<li>{{ a }}</li>{% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% endif %}
    {% if rcs %}
    <p class="disclaimer">Baseline DP gap before permutation: <strong>{{ "%.3f" | format(rcs.baseline_dp_gap) }}</strong>. {{ rc.disclaimer }}</p>
    {% else %}
    <p class="disclaimer">{{ rc.disclaimer }}</p>
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if report.result.india_metrics %}
    {% set im = report.result.india_metrics %}
    <h2>7. India-specific metrics (RBI-aligned)</h2>
    {% if im.spls %}
    <h3>Sub-Plan Lending Shortfall (SPLS)</h3>
    <p>Source: RBI Master Directions on Priority Sector Lending. Lower is better — gaps indicate under-allocation against the regulatory sub-target.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Group</th><th class="num">Actual %</th><th class="num">Target %</th><th class="num">Shortfall %</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for g, actual in im.spls.actual_pct_by_group.items() %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ g }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.2f" | format(actual) }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.2f" | format(im.spls.target_pct_by_group.get(g, 0.0)) }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.2f" | format(im.spls.shortfall_pct_by_group.get(g, 0.0)) }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Worst-shortfall group: <code>{{ im.spls.worst_group or "—" }}</code>. Total shortfall amount across groups: <strong>{{ "%.2f" | format(im.spls.total_shortfall_amount) }}</strong>.</p>
    {% endif %}
    {% if im.lrb %}
    <h3>Loan Rejection Bias (LRB)</h3>
    <p>Source: RBI Digital Lending Directions §8. Ratio &lt; 0.80 trips the 4/5ths advisory.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Group</th><th class="num">Rejection rate</th><th class="num">n</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for g, rate in im.lrb.rejection_rate_by_group.items() %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ g }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ "%.1f%%" | format(rate * 100) }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ im.lrb.n_by_group.get(g, 0) }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Worst-best ratio: <strong>{{ "%.3f" | format(im.lrb.rejection_rate_ratio) }}</strong>
       <span class="badge {% if im.lrb.rbi_advisory_breach %}fail{% else %}pass{% endif %}">
         {% if im.lrb.rbi_advisory_breach %}breach{% else %}within advisory{% endif %}
       </span>
       — worst group: <code>{{ im.lrb.worst_group or "—" }}</code>.</p>
    {% endif %}
    {% if im.dlf %}
    <h3>Digital Lending Fairness (DLF) composite</h3>
    <p>Source: RBIH Fairness Lab Framework v1 (2024).</p>
    <dl class="kv">
      <dt>Composite score</dt><dd><strong>{{ "%.3f" | format(im.dlf.score) }}</strong> / 1.000</dd>
      <dt>Disparate impact</dt><dd>{{ "%.3f" | format(im.dlf.disparate_impact) }}</dd>
      <dt>Equal opportunity</dt><dd>{{ "%.3f" | format(im.dlf.equal_opportunity) }}</dd>
      <dt>Calibration within groups</dt><dd>{{ "%.3f" | format(im.dlf.calibration_within_groups) }}</dd>
    </dl>
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if report.result.intersectional %}
    <h2>8. Intersectional slices</h2>
    <p>Compounded disparities at the intersection of two or more protected attributes (e.g. caste × gender). These often hide inside per-attribute marginals — Dalit women, for instance, can be worse off than either the &ldquo;Dalit&rdquo; or &ldquo;women&rdquo; aggregate suggests.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Slice</th><th>Metric</th><th class="num">Value</th><th class="num">n</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for m in report.result.intersectional %}
        <tr>
          <td><code>{{ m.slice_key }}</code></td>
          <td>{{ m.metric }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ m.value | fmt_ratio }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ m.sample_size }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="annex">
      <h2>Annex A — Regulatory mapping</h2>
      {% if report.request.regime == "DPDP" %}
      <p><strong>Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 &amp; DPDP Rules 2025 — Rule 13 DPIA</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>§5 Notice — consent screen and purpose declaration captured in the audit request.</li>
        <li>§7 Purpose limitation — audit performed within declared purpose only.</li>
        <li>§8(3) Accuracy &amp; minimisation — schema validated, no raw PII processed (Sensitive Data Protection templates applied where applicable).</li>
        <li>§8(5) Security safeguards — CMEK, VPC-SC, Model Armor (refer to <code>docs/SECURITY.md</code>).</li>
        <li>§8(6) Breach notification — 72h pipeline wired via the Watcher agent.</li>
        <li>Rule 13 DPIA — this report itself constitutes the DPIA artifact.</li>
      </ul>
      {% elif report.request.regime == "EU_AI_ACT" %}
      <p><strong>EU AI Act (Regulation (EU) 2024/1689) — high-risk AI systems</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Art. 9 Risk management — risk register attached.</li>
        <li>Art. 10 Data governance — representativeness + bias examination evidenced by the slice table above.</li>
        <li>Art. 13 Transparency — this report is the instructions-for-use artifact.</li>
        <li>Art. 14 Human oversight — reviewer approval required before sign-off.</li>
        <li>Art. 15 Accuracy, robustness, cybersecurity — evaluation gate ≥ 95% on Genkit evals; Model Armor on all Gemini calls.</li>
      </ul>
      {% elif report.request.regime == "RBI" %}
      <p><strong>RBI Digital Lending Directions 2025</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Fair practices — disparate-impact check above.</li>
        <li>Grievance redress — Ombudsman role available.</li>
        <li>Data localisation — asia-south1 (Mumbai) primary; asia-south2 (Delhi) DR.</li>
      </ul>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <footer>
      Generated by NyayaAI at {{ generated_at }}.
      Audit ID: {{ report.request.audit_id }}.
      Apache-2.0 · GSC 2026 submission.
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
